evaluation of the slac response to questions from epac page 1 evaluation of the slac response to questions from epac we the undersigned members of the epac reviewed the response of the e163 experiment to the questions raised at the september 2001 meeting of the slac epac we are satisfied with the response and consider that all the issues raised by the committee have been addressed appropriately by the experiment including questions concerning jitter and beam optics in particular we would like to commend the quality and invested effort of the start to end simulation of the experiment given this additional input we believe that the proposal now provides an appropriate level of assurance of success we have already observed the importance of the accelerator physics addressed by the experiment and its significance as a step towards the orion facility ilan ben zvi tor raubenheimer david rice
